The big problem mages face is that pets take xp if they out damage, but over burning blows mana (higher resists maybe fizzles to? since we specialize in EITHER fire or magic nukes, not both, compared to a wiz)<br>
<br>
So what you do is pull the mob, sic pet, usually an earth pet. It maybe buffed, when pet's low in health and you are in command range, you start casting another pet, and pre-type /pet get lost . At last fraction of spell, say 1/3rd bubb, you hit enter key, old pet that's badly damaged is replaced by a new one. When mob is low health you can Reclaim Energy pet, and nuke-kill mob for full xp.<br>
<br>
very very efficient, for example its 325 mana for my 1005 hp nuke, or 400 mana for 57 earth pet.<br>
<br>
However it is *not* easy  bad connection, lag, any screw up and you have no pet and a very POd mob.<br>
