<br>
I did not get root until level 34.  I was very relieved when I finally picked it up - almost as happy as I was the first time I got invis on my wizard (waiting until level *16* really hurt).<br>
<br>
I would take the defensive capability granted by root over the defensive ability granted by a pet (admittedly necro pets do not have the same strength as mage pets).  But having access to both, I would choose root over a pet, hands down, every time.  And wizards also have stuns, something I have yet to see mentioned in a defensive capability. <p>-Arbaon</p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10>Class Balance & Class Bugs</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  